    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The most common variety of Maori pounamu stone that comes in many shades, from strong rich green to dark green; often a translucent nephrite. It is often characterized by small dark inclusions, which is considered an addition to its character.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
